    BENEFIT OF EXTENDED SURVEILLANCE OF LOW-RISK PANCREATIC CYSTS AFTER FIVE-YEAR STABILITY: A SYSTEMATIC REVIEW AND META-ANALYSIS.
 A lower incidence of advanced neoplasia during extended surveillance among low-risk, stable-sized BD-IPMNs is a key finding of this study. However, the survival benefit of surveillance among this population warrants further exploration through high-quality studies before recommending surveillance cessation with certainty.
